def _cython_agg_blocks(
    self, how: str, alt=None, numeric_only: bool = True, min_count: int = -1
) -> "Tuple[List[Block], Index]":

    data: BlockManager = self._get_data_to_aggregate()

    if numeric_only:
        data = data._get_numeric_data()
    # Handle nullable integer data type appropriately
    if isinstance(data, pd.DataFrame) and data.dtypes.all() == 'Int64':
        data = data.dropna()

    # Perform aggregation with the appropriate handling for nullable integer data type
    aggregated_data = data.aggregate(how, axis=1, min_count=min_count)

    # Construct the resulting agg_blocks and agg_items based on the aggregated data
    agg_blocks = [Block(result) for result in aggregated_data]
    agg_items = data.columns

    return agg_blocks, agg_items
